\ basic
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 3 take .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 take .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 5 take .

\ clamp: n > length yields the whole array
[ 1 2 3 ] 99 take .

\ clamp: negative n yields the empty array
[ 1 2 3 ] -2 take .

\ empty source
[ ] 3 take .

\ set source produces an array of the first n in sorted order
{ 5 1 3 2 4 } 3 take .

\ result is consumed: stack shape is ( source n -- result )
1 2 3 [ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 take .
.s

\ composes with other words
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 4 take cardinality .
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 3 take reverse .

\ failures
[ 1 2 3 ] "x" take
[ 1 2 3 ] take
5 3 take
